    "In this case, the BERTScore output is 0.834 under the optimal threshold, resulting in a labeled mismatch with the ground truth.Our study revealed an interesting observation regarding the potential of GPT as a promising and unique tool to assess the accuracy of generated text compared to the ground truth.",
    "Notably, GPT evaluators can leverage their pre-trained knowledge base to evaluate text based not only on lexical similarity but also on semantic similarity.",
    "This ability effectively addresses some significant limitations of existing NLP metrics.",
    "To illustrate, consider the extracted intervention for record 26 as an example (Supplementary Material 6).",
    "The labeled ground truth is \"Pre-emptive use of proton pump inhibitors (PPI),\" while the generated output of GPT-4.0 is \"Pre-emptive PPI (intravenous esomeprazole followed by high-dose oral esomeprazole).\""
